              '<p>This week&rsquo;s meditation introduces a mantra that coordinates with the breath&mdash;<em>so ham</em>. The literal meaning of this mantra is &ldquo;<em>sah aham</em>&mdash;I am That,&rdquo; meaning &ldquo;I am the flow of consciousness that sustains the flow of breath and life.&rdquo; This recording introduces the mantra, but you may want to sit longer with meditation using the mantra (you may be up to 20 minutes this week). Also consider using the mantra in your daily personal practice, and allow the mantra to come forward in your mind in guided breath awareness meditations, even if not specifically instructed to remember the mantra.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><a href="https://yogainternational.com/ecourse/6-week-meditation-challenge/6/2">Guided Meditation with So Ham Mantra</a>, audio with Sandra Anderson</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can read more about this mantra and also mantra meditation in general in the two excellent articles by Pandit Tigunait and Swami Rama. They also offer practical tips and inspiration to support and enrich your meditation. If you ever forget the importance of meditation, read these and hurry to your meditation seat!</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><a href="https://yogainternational.com/ecourse/6-week-meditation-challenge/6/3">How to Train Your Mind to Support a Meditation Practice</a>, Q&amp;A with Pandit Rajmani Tigunait&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li><a href="https://yogainternational.com/ecourse/6-week-meditation-challenge/6/4">Meditation is Not What You Think</a>, article by Swami Rama</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Though this 40-day challenge is coming to an end, your study and practice are ongoing. Here are a few suggestions for delving in a bit deeper.</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><em><a href="https://shop.yogainternational.com/products/meditation-and-its-practice-by-swami-rama">Meditation and Its Practice</a>&nbsp;</em></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Written by Swami Rama, the founder of the Himalayan Institute, this is an elegant and straightforward book that includes all the basics to strengthen your foundation.</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><a href="http://shop.himalayaninstitute.org/products/power-of-mantra-and-mystery-of-initiation"><em>Power of Mantra and Mystery of Initiation</em></a>, by Pandit Rajmani Tigunait</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Panditji is Swami Rama&rsquo;s successor, and this is simply the best-ever introduction to mantra meditation. It includes descriptions of the different kinds of mantras and how they are used, mantra initiation and how it works, and a beautiful explanation of the power of the so&rsquo;ham mantra.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><a href="https://yogainternational.com/article/view/heal-yourself-heal-the-world-a-mantra-for-peace-and-prosperity">The Maha Mrityunjaya Mantra</a>, by Rolf Sovik</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>This article includes an audio download of Panditji teaching the Maha Mrityunjaya mantra and instructions for its practice.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>And finally, here is a complete practice in 40 minutes. It includes asana, breath awareness, a guided relaxation, and a short guided meditation.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><a href="https://yogainternational.com/ecourse/6-week-meditation-challenge/6/5">The Complete Package: Move, Relax, and Meditate, with Sandra Anderson</a>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Thank you for joining us!</p>',
